author_ssm: Finding aid prepared by Brendan Dolan and Nicole Greenhouse
unittitle_ssm: Mick Moloney Irish-American Music and Popular Culture Videotapes
abstract_ssm: These videotapes are part of the larger Mick Moloney Irish-American Music and Popular Culture Collection.  This sub-collection consists of VHS cassettes, Beta videocassette tapes, and U-Matic videocassettes acquired in the course of Dr. Moloney's career as a folklorist, producer, musician, and academic.  The tapes include amateur and professional recordings of Dr. Moloney's performances, extensive documentation of the 1987 International Village Fair, commercial videotapes collected as teaching aids, and videotapes used as masters and safeties for recording sessions.
